✨ Surah Al-Kafirun✨

📖 Taruf aur Nuzool ka Waqiya

➡️ Surah Al-Kafirun ek Makki Surah hai, isme 6 ayaat hain.
➡️ Jab Nabi ﷺ ne khule aam Islam ki dawat di to Quraysh ke leaders pareshan hue.
➡️ Abu Jahl, Walid bin Mughirah aur kuch aur mushrikeen ne Nabi ﷺ se samjhota (compromise) karne ki koshish ki.
➡️ Unhone kaha:

Ek saal aap hamare buton ki ibadat karen.
Ek saal hum aapke Rabb ki ibadat karenge.

➡️ Is tarah dono taraf “izzat” barabar rahegi.
➡️ Jawab mein Allah ne ye surah nazil ki aur saaf keh diya ke Haq aur Baatil kabhi ek nahi ho sakte.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

📝 Ayat by Ayat Roman Urdu Tarjuma + Tafsir

                                                        🌸بِسْمِ اللّٰہِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِیْمِ🌸
                                                        Bismillaahir-Rahmaanir-Raheem
                              ➡️ “Allah ke Naam se shuru karta hoon, jo bohot Meherbaan aur Nihayat Reham Karne Wala hai.”


1️⃣ Qul yaa ayyuhal kaafiroon
➡️ “Keh do (Aey Nabi ﷺ): Aey kaafiron!”
👉 Allah ne Nabi ﷺ ko direct order diya ke mushrikeen se baat saaf taur par keh do.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2️⃣ Laa a’budu maa ta’budoon
➡️ “Main unki ibadat nahi karta jin ki tum ibadat karte ho.”
👉 Yani main tumhare buton ki ibadat nahi karta, na ab karta hoon aur na kabhi karunga.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3️⃣ Wa laa antum ‘aabidoona maa a’bud
➡️ “Aur tum uski ibadat nahi karte jise main ibadat karta hoon.”
👉 Tum log sirf Allah ki ibadat karne wale nahi ho, kyunki tum shirk ke saath mile hue ho.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

4️⃣ Wa laa ana ‘abidum maa ‘abattum
➡️ “Aur na main ibadat karne wala hoon unki jin ki tum ibadat karte ho.”
👉 Is ayat mein aur zyada ta’keed hai ke “kabhi bhi” main tumhare buton ki ibadat nahi karunga.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

5️⃣ Wa laa antum ‘aabidoona maa a’bud
➡️ “Aur tum ibadat karne wale nahi ho uski jise main ibadat karta hoon.”
👉 Phir se is baat ko dohraya gaya taake baat bilkul wazeh ho jaye.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

6️⃣ Lakum deenukum wa liya deen
➡️ “Tumhare liye tumhara deen, aur mere liye mera deen.”
👉 Yani tum apne shirk par raho (agar rehna chahte ho), main apne deen (Islam, tauheed) par qaim hoon.
👉 Ye jumla separation aur final decision ka izhaar hai – koi compromise nahi.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

💡 Tafseeli Hikmat aur Maqsad

➡️ Haq aur Baatil ko mix nahi kiya jaa sakta. Islam sirf tauheed sikhata hai.
➡️ Ibadat ka asal matlab sirf Allah ki bandagi hai, aur shirk ka isme koi hissa nahi.
➡️ Freedom of choice: Islam kehta hai – tum apna deen raho, main apna deen. Zabardasti nahi. Lekin sachai ek hi hai.
➡️ Ikhlaas aur purity: Musalman ko apni ibadat mein sirf Allah ko khaalis rakhna hai.
➡️ Final separation line: Ye surah Muslim aur non-Muslim ke darmiyan boundary clear karti hai.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🌸 Sabak jo Hum Seekhte Hain

➡️ Apne aqeede mein kabhi compromise na karo.
➡️ Maashray ka pressure ya logon ki dosti ke liye shirk ya ghalat kaam mat karo.
➡️ Islam izzat aur mazbooti ka deen hai, jisme koi bargaining nahi.
➡️ Hume har amal sirf Allah ke liye khaalis karna chahiye.
➡️ “Lakum deenukum wa liya deen” ka matlab ye bhi hai ke insaan apna hisaab khud dega – isliye apni ibadat ko saaf rakho.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

📘 Surah Al-Kafirun ki Ahmiyat

➡️ Nabi ﷺ is surah ko bohot pasand karte the.
➡️ Aap ﷺ fajar ki sunnat aur maghrib ki sunnat mein is surah ko padhtay the.
➡️ Ye surah shirk se barā’at (alag rehne) ki surah hai.

